
UTF-16: 16bits
not suitable for ASCII based OS, text-processing soft. Use 16 bits for all char.

UTF-8 encode all ASCII chars using the same bytes as in  ASCII.
0000-007F: 1bytes
0080-07FF: 2
0800-FFFF: 3
10000-10FFFF:4

Compress Unicode: SCSU , BOCU-1

Standard compression scheme for Unicode
Big-endian UTF-16(UTF16-16BE)

BOCU-1: binary ordered compression of Unicode

Big-endian: Start with FE FF  0061  (end at most-significant end)
little-endian: FF FE 6100 (least significant end)
